1
00:00:02,208 --> 00:00:03,625
[wind howling]

2
00:00:03,708 --> 00:00:06,208
- Since everybody's taking
shelter in the graveyard now,

3
00:00:06,291 --> 00:00:08,791
I guess that means
you finished the trial.

4
00:00:08,875 --> 00:00:10,125
That's awesome.

5
00:00:10,208 --> 00:00:12,291
Great job, Mili. [gasps]

6
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:16,916
- Is she--
- Subaru!

7
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:20,083
Focus your attention
here for now, I suppose!

8
00:00:21,375 --> 00:00:22,791
Why are you
suddenly acting so strange?

9
00:00:22,875 --> 00:00:25,666
- Oh, uh,
hearing you call me "Subaru"

10
00:00:25,750 --> 00:00:27,291
is still kinda new to me,

11
00:00:27,375 --> 00:00:29,208
so I was
just basking in it a little.

12
00:00:29,291 --> 00:00:30,208
- Save that for later,
I suppose...

13
00:00:30,291 --> 00:00:32,166
Subaru.

14
00:00:32,250 --> 00:00:35,250
- Damn. You are just so cute!
- [grumbles]

15
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:38,333
- It looks like we're about to
go up against the Great Rabbit.

16
00:00:38,416 --> 00:00:39,083
Are you ready for this?

17
00:00:39,166 --> 00:00:41,333
- The contract
was only just signed,

18
00:00:41,416 --> 00:00:43,291
and it's one
of the Three Great Mabeasts.

19
00:00:43,375 --> 00:00:45,458
The contractor's quite a novice.

20
00:00:45,541 --> 00:00:46,333
Plus it's been 400 years

21
00:00:46,416 --> 00:00:48,291
since I was involved
in a battle, I suppose.

22
00:00:48,375 --> 00:00:50,250
- And?

23
00:00:52,541 --> 00:00:55,291
- I'd call this situation
the perfect handicap.

24
00:00:55,375 --> 00:00:56,750
- [chittering]

25
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:59,125
[gnashing teeth echoing]

26
00:00:59,208 --> 00:01:00,791
- Are you getting scared?

27
00:01:00,875 --> 00:01:03,416
- Oh, no. There's not a chance.

28
00:01:06,541 --> 00:01:10,166
Emilia's behind me,
and you're beside me.

29
00:01:10,250 --> 00:01:12,541
This is the strongest I've
ever felt in my whole life!

30
00:01:12,625 --> 00:01:14,541
- That's the spirit.

31
00:01:14,625 --> 00:01:16,166
- [chittering]

32
00:01:18,583 --> 00:01:21,375
-<i> El Minya!</i>

33
00:01:29,416 --> 00:01:31,541
- Holy crap!

34
00:01:31,625 --> 00:01:33,250
So what should I do to help?!

35
00:01:33,333 --> 00:01:35,083
- For starters,
just keep holding my hand,

36
00:01:35,166 --> 00:01:37,541
and don't leave me alone,
I suppose.

37
00:01:37,625 --> 00:01:39,541
Now close your eyes.

38
00:01:39,625 --> 00:01:41,666
Begin imagining yourself
weaving mana

39
00:01:41,750 --> 00:01:43,166
and shaping your power
into arrows,

40
00:01:43,250 --> 00:01:45,791
crushing the enemy
in a single supreme attack.

41
00:01:45,875 --> 00:01:46,666
- Done! Okay!
- Good!

42
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:48,833
Then just say it, I suppose!

43
00:01:48,916 --> 00:01:50,458
BOTH:<i> El Minya!</i>

44
00:01:55,291 --> 00:01:56,416
BEATRICE: Cross over!

45
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,375
- Got it!

46
00:01:58,541 --> 00:01:59,166
- [chittering]

47
00:01:59,250 --> 00:02:01,375
BEATRICE: Take the left,
I suppose!

48
00:02:01,458 --> 00:02:03,000
SUBARU:
And the right's all yours!

49
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:05,541
<i>Minya!</i>

50
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:07,500
<i>Minya! Minya!</i>

51
00:02:07,583 --> 00:02:09,833
That's hard to say!

52
00:02:09,916 --> 00:02:11,041
<i>Minya!</i>

53
00:02:12,708 --> 00:02:14,750
These things keep coming!
What's the plan?

54
00:02:14,833 --> 00:02:16,875
- What we need to do now
is gather all of them

55
00:02:16,958 --> 00:02:18,541
in one place, right here.

56
00:02:18,625 --> 00:02:19,166
- Huh?

57
00:02:19,250 --> 00:02:21,333
- While they may be infinite,

58
00:02:21,416 --> 00:02:23,833
they still have
an upper limit, I suppose,

59
00:02:23,916 --> 00:02:25,583
so they can only multiply
up to a certain number,

60
00:02:25,666 --> 00:02:27,708
which means...

61
00:02:27,791 --> 00:02:29,541
- By stopping them
when they hit that number,

62
00:02:29,625 --> 00:02:31,375
we should be able
to take 'em down!

63
00:02:31,458 --> 00:02:33,416
- But the question
is how to do it.

64
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:34,833
- Think you might be forgetting.

65
00:02:34,916 --> 00:02:37,708
It's not like the two of us
have
to solve this problem alone.

66
00:02:37,791 --> 00:02:38,625
- Huh?

67
00:02:38,708 --> 00:02:40,583
The things you say...

68
00:02:40,666 --> 00:02:42,250
[scoffs]

69
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:43,833
While I'm getting
everything ready,

70
00:02:43,916 --> 00:02:45,625
act as a decoy, I suppose.

71
00:02:45,708 --> 00:02:46,500
- Not a problem.

72
00:02:46,583 --> 00:02:48,416
When it comes
to being bait for the enemy,

73
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:52,208
there's no one in Lugunica
who's
better at doing that than me!

74
00:02:53,666 --> 00:02:55,458
Hmph.

75
00:02:55,541 --> 00:02:56,708
[wind howling]

76
00:02:56,791 --> 00:02:59,416
[Subaru panting]

77
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:01,375
Hey, Great Rabbit!

78
00:03:01,458 --> 00:03:04,750
It's me! You know you want some,
so come and get it!

79
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:06,125
Uhp! Too slow!

80
00:03:08,791 --> 00:03:10,416
Mili!

81
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:13,250
Beatrice and I are gonna
knock all these bastards out!

82
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:16,291
[pants] And I was hoping
you could help us a little!

83
00:03:16,375 --> 00:03:17,750
- EMILIA: Subaru?!
- Listen up!

84
00:03:17,833 --> 00:03:19,666
I know I'm probably
asking too much of you,

85
00:03:19,750 --> 00:03:20,541
and if you can't do it,

86
00:03:20,625 --> 00:03:22,625
I'll try and come up
with something else.

87
00:03:22,708 --> 00:03:25,583
But if you can, then I
want you to give it a shot!

88
00:03:25,666 --> 00:03:27,541
Let's win this thing together!

89
00:03:29,625 --> 00:03:30,833
- Okay! Count on me,

90
00:03:30,916 --> 00:03:32,791
and I'll count on you!

91
00:03:32,875 --> 00:03:34,750
- Hell, yeah! I'm all over it!

92
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:39,333
[yells]

93
00:03:41,541 --> 00:03:44,625
Now's our one chance, Emilia!
Trace the line!

94
00:03:44,708 --> 00:03:46,458
- You're doing so well...

95
00:03:46,541 --> 00:03:47,958
like you always do!

96
00:03:51,166 --> 00:03:53,333
I'm not letting
any of you escape!

97
00:03:56,541 --> 00:03:58,708
- Holy crap.

98
00:04:01,125 --> 00:04:02,291
Sucks for you!

99
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:03,916
I'd say the time's
just about run out

100
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,500
for you little monsters!

101
00:04:05,583 --> 00:04:07,583
[gasps] Okay.

102
00:04:07,666 --> 00:04:09,333
Everything's
in your hands now...

103
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:11,500
Great Spirit Beatrice!

104
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:13,750
- Hmph.

105
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:15,583
<i>Al Shamac.</i>

106
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:20,500
[energy surging]

107
00:04:20,583 --> 00:04:22,208
[chittering]

108
00:04:40,625 --> 00:04:41,708
- We did it.

109
00:04:41,791 --> 00:04:44,833
- That was just amazing.

110
00:04:44,916 --> 00:04:47,625
- I sent each one of them
to an isolated space

111
00:04:47,708 --> 00:04:49,583
similar to
the forbidden library.

112
00:04:49,666 --> 00:04:51,708
They'll never be able to make
their way back out, I suppose.

113
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:55,041
[villagers cheering]

114
00:04:57,125 --> 00:04:58,750
[sad music playing]

115
00:05:03,708 --> 00:05:04,833
[Roswaal winces]

116
00:05:04,916 --> 00:05:07,000
[crying]

117
00:05:16,625 --> 00:05:18,833
- Subaru, look.

118
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:25,750
- You've nothing to say
to the one who just managed to--

119
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:27,500
- [wails]
- You really did it!

120
00:05:27,583 --> 00:05:28,791
I knew you could!
I love you, Beako!

121
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:31,958
- Let me go, I suppose!

122
00:05:32,041 --> 00:05:34,666
- That's my girl!
You're so cute!

123
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:35,708
- [villagers laughing]
- Beako's amazing!

124
00:05:35,791 --> 00:05:36,708
- Beako's the best!
- Suba--

125
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:40,083
- Beako for life! [laughs]
- Subaru!

126
00:05:40,166 --> 00:05:43,625
[Subaru whoops]

127
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:47,416
[breeze echoing]

128
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,666
BEATRICE:
I'm really sorry, Mother.

129
00:05:55,750 --> 00:05:59,708
I tried, but I couldn't
keep my promise to you.

130
00:05:59,791 --> 00:06:00,625
- You say that, yet it looks

131
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:04,000
as if a weight
was lifted from your shoulders.

132
00:06:04,083 --> 00:06:07,458
- You don't seem like yourself,
either, I suppose.

133
00:06:07,541 --> 00:06:09,916
I was under the impression
that encountering Mother

134
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,875
was your bloodline's
greatest wish.

135
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:16,625
- May I ask you something?

136
00:06:16,708 --> 00:06:18,916
- Hmm?
- Was it ultimately Subaru

137
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,875
who proved to be
"that person" for you?

138
00:06:21,958 --> 00:06:25,958
- Hmph! He isn't suited for it
in any way, shape, or form,

139
00:06:26,041 --> 00:06:28,666
but that's fine with me.

140
00:06:28,750 --> 00:06:30,666
I chose Subaru

141
00:06:30,750 --> 00:06:32,541
even though he's
not "that person," I suppose.

142
00:06:32,625 --> 00:06:34,708
- Why?

143
00:06:34,791 --> 00:06:37,583
- Because when I sincerely
asked him to take on that role,

144
00:06:37,666 --> 00:06:38,500
he just started laughing.

145
00:06:38,583 --> 00:06:41,625
Then he insisted
he could make me much happier

146
00:06:41,708 --> 00:06:43,958
than some random stranger
I wouldn't even recognize

147
00:06:44,041 --> 00:06:45,125
ever could, I suppose.

148
00:06:45,208 --> 00:06:46,958
- Sounds like him.

149
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:48,958
That's quite an arrogant answer.

150
00:06:49,041 --> 00:06:51,083
- But I don't really hate
how pushy he can be.

151
00:06:51,166 --> 00:06:53,583
- You're sure about this?

152
00:06:53,666 --> 00:06:56,000
Even though you know you won't
ever be his first priority?

153
00:06:56,083 --> 00:06:59,500
- You seem to be confused,
I suppose.

154
00:06:59,583 --> 00:07:01,666
I didn't leave
the forbidden library

155
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:04,916
'cause I became number one
in Subaru's mind.

156
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,750
I left that place for
an entirely different reason.

157
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:10,083
I want to make him
<i>my</i> number one.

158
00:07:10,166 --> 00:07:12,041
-<i> Choose me, Beatrice.</i>

159
00:07:14,791 --> 00:07:16,291
- [chuckles]

160
00:07:16,375 --> 00:07:19,666
No matter how old you get,
you never change, now, do you?

161
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:20,875
The same as always.

162
00:07:20,958 --> 00:07:22,083
- Huh?

163
00:07:22,166 --> 00:07:23,458
- My apologies.

164
00:07:23,541 --> 00:07:26,416
You and I really haven't
spoken enough, have we?

165
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:30,666
Not in all the time
since we were both with Teacher.

166
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:32,166
- What do you mean by that?

167
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:36,666
[gasps] Are you<i> the</i> Roswaal?

168
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:38,208
- Well, of course.
Who else would I be?

169
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:41,083
- No! No!
That's not what I meant!

170
00:07:41,166 --> 00:07:43,041
- I was only joking.

171
00:07:43,125 --> 00:07:44,208
It's true.

172
00:07:44,291 --> 00:07:48,958
I am that Roswaal, Beatrice.

173
00:07:49,041 --> 00:07:51,750
- You mean
by soul transcription?

174
00:07:51,833 --> 00:07:54,541
From Mother's attempts
to try and live forever?

175
00:07:54,625 --> 00:07:56,083
But every one of them failed!

176
00:07:56,166 --> 00:07:58,750
- The soul of another won't
take hold in an empty vessel,

177
00:07:58,833 --> 00:08:02,333
so rather than use someone
else,
you need only prepare a vessel

178
00:08:02,416 --> 00:08:05,833
that has high affinity
with the pursuer's soul.

179
00:08:07,291 --> 00:08:09,541
- [gasps]

180
00:08:09,625 --> 00:08:11,708
- Tell me, do you feel
I'm some kind of monster?

181
00:08:11,791 --> 00:08:14,041
- [gasps]

182
00:08:17,875 --> 00:08:19,875
Kneel down right there,
I suppose.

183
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:21,875
- Kneel down, you say?

184
00:08:24,041 --> 00:08:25,916
- Now brace yourself.

185
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,708
- [gasps]

186
00:08:27,791 --> 00:08:29,500
[groans]

187
00:08:30,833 --> 00:08:31,625
I presume that was your way

188
00:08:31,708 --> 00:08:35,000
of showing contempt
for my dubious actions?

189
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:36,250
- Certainly not.
I neither know nor care

190
00:08:36,333 --> 00:08:38,375
why it is
you want to be reprimanded.

191
00:08:38,458 --> 00:08:41,083
That was obviously payback
for burning down

192
00:08:41,166 --> 00:08:42,916
the forbidden library,
I suppose.

193
00:08:47,958 --> 00:08:49,250
BEATRICE:<i> This childish</i>
<i>infatuation of yours</i>

194
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:50,583
<i>would cause nothing</i>
<i>but trouble for Mother.</i>

195
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:51,916
ECHIDNA:
<i>All three of you are here?</i>

196
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,125
RYUZU:<i> I'd be happy</i>
<i>for the opportunity...</i>

197
00:08:53,208 --> 00:08:54,041
<i>- Naturally, I suppose.</i>
<i>- So says Beatrice,</i>

198
00:08:54,125 --> 00:08:55,750
<i>echoing the same words</i>
<i>her teacher used.</i>

199
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:57,916
<i>All right.</i>
<i>Then how about, "I love you"?</i>

200
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,375
BEATRICE: Roswaal...

201
00:09:00,458 --> 00:09:01,500
- Yes?

202
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,625
- Welcome back.

203
00:09:04,708 --> 00:09:07,083
- Yes. That's right.

204
00:09:07,166 --> 00:09:10,500
<i>I'm back, Beatrice.</i>

205
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:14,875
<i>And welcome home.</i>

206
00:09:14,958 --> 00:09:17,458
[music playing]

207
00:09:42,166 --> 00:09:43,416
[breeze blowing]

208
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:46,666
EMILIA: They still
haven't come out of there.

209
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:47,875
- Yeah,
but I'm sure they're fine.

210
00:09:47,958 --> 00:09:49,958
- [laughs]

211
00:09:50,041 --> 00:09:52,416
Your trust in Beatrice
has grown quite a bit.

212
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:55,000
But you two were always
good friends, weren't you?

213
00:09:55,083 --> 00:09:56,458
- Both now and then,

214
00:09:56,541 --> 00:09:58,416
I don't know if you'd
exactly call us "friends."

215
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:01,708
- [energy chimes]
- Hey, is that Puck?

216
00:10:01,791 --> 00:10:03,208
[chiming continues]

217
00:10:03,291 --> 00:10:04,791
I'd like to thank him
for his help,

218
00:10:04,875 --> 00:10:06,583
but he's still
pretty zonked out, isn't he?

219
00:10:06,666 --> 00:10:09,250
- He's exhausted. I guess
with everything that happened,

220
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:10,666
he overdid it a little.

221
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:12,166
And even having
this stone to occupy

222
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:13,666
isn't enough to wake him up.

223
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:16,291
- But you'll definitely
call him back someday, though.

224
00:10:16,375 --> 00:10:16,750
- Right?

225
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:19,208
- [gasps]

226
00:10:19,291 --> 00:10:20,708
Of course.

227
00:10:22,416 --> 00:10:26,291
- I've gotta say
you've changed, Mili.

228
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:28,500
You seem so much stronger.

229
00:10:28,583 --> 00:10:32,041
- If I am, then it's only
thanks to you and everyone else,

230
00:10:32,125 --> 00:10:34,416
since all I ever do
is take, anyway.

231
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:38,041
I need to get to a point where
I can give back to others soon.

232
00:10:38,125 --> 00:10:39,541
- [chuckles] Well,
it's funny you should say that.

233
00:10:39,625 --> 00:10:43,708
I feel like all I ever do
is take, too. [laughs]

234
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:46,875
- By the way, Subaru, I...

235
00:10:46,958 --> 00:10:48,000
I wanted to...

236
00:10:48,083 --> 00:10:50,000
- Huh? What's up?

237
00:10:50,083 --> 00:10:53,083
Your face just turned beet red
all of a sudden. You okay?

238
00:10:53,166 --> 00:10:55,458
Uh, I'm okay, totally fine.

239
00:10:55,541 --> 00:10:57,916
Anyway, there's something
important I wanted to discuss.

240
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:00,083
- Eh, what is it?

241
00:11:00,166 --> 00:11:01,791
You're acting
pretty weird right now.

242
00:11:01,875 --> 00:11:04,583
- Well, just so I'm sure...

243
00:11:04,666 --> 00:11:08,250
you said that you--
that you loved me, right?

244
00:11:08,333 --> 00:11:10,291
- [gasps] Uh, yes, I did!

245
00:11:10,375 --> 00:11:11,125
I do, so much!

246
00:11:11,208 --> 00:11:12,541
- Good. Um...

247
00:11:12,625 --> 00:11:16,333
that, uh, makes me
really, really happy.

248
00:11:16,416 --> 00:11:18,708
That said, I, uh...

249
00:11:18,791 --> 00:11:21,625
think we should have
an important conversation.

250
00:11:23,083 --> 00:11:25,375
You see...

251
00:11:25,458 --> 00:11:28,000
I wanted to talk about...

252
00:11:28,083 --> 00:11:29,958
[whimpers]

253
00:11:30,041 --> 00:11:32,000
the baby that's in my belly!

254
00:11:33,125 --> 00:11:36,125
- Excuse me?

255
00:11:36,208 --> 00:11:36,958
- I-I'm still not sure

256
00:11:37,041 --> 00:11:38,583
if it's a boy or a girl
at this point,

257
00:11:38,666 --> 00:11:40,583
and I know that it's
a big responsibility,

258
00:11:40,666 --> 00:11:43,916
but I don't have a clue
about this kind of thing.

259
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,416
So I-I figured I had to talk
to the father about it.

260
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:48,041
- Whoa, whoa, wait a minute!

261
00:11:48,125 --> 00:11:50,125
Mili, you've seriously
got to slow down here!

262
00:11:50,208 --> 00:11:52,833
You just said that--
you said, "a baby," right?

263
00:11:52,916 --> 00:11:54,375
- Y-Yes, exactly!
I know it won't be easy

264
00:11:54,458 --> 00:11:56,958
with the royal selection
going on,

265
00:11:57,041 --> 00:11:58,000
but that's not the baby's fault!

266
00:11:58,083 --> 00:12:01,083
I just want to do my best
and make our child happy!

267
00:12:01,166 --> 00:12:03,875
[light music playing]

268
00:12:03,958 --> 00:12:05,291
- Listen.

269
00:12:05,375 --> 00:12:07,458
Babies aren't delivered
to you by storks, you know.

270
00:12:07,541 --> 00:12:09,958
And they aren't grown in
magical cabbage fields, either.

271
00:12:10,041 --> 00:12:11,458
- Well, obviously!
I'm aware of that!

272
00:12:11,541 --> 00:12:13,833
They're made when a boy and girl
kiss on the lips, right?

273
00:12:13,916 --> 00:12:15,458
- Huh?

274
00:12:16,583 --> 00:12:17,458
[stammers]

275
00:12:17,541 --> 00:12:18,125
[energy chimes]

276
00:12:18,208 --> 00:12:19,208
SUBARU: Damn it!

277
00:12:19,291 --> 00:12:21,958
I hate you, Puck!

278
00:12:25,041 --> 00:12:26,208
[birds chirping]

279
00:12:26,291 --> 00:12:27,375
[Garfiel yells]

280
00:12:31,041 --> 00:12:32,041
Nice one. Right in the face!

281
00:12:32,125 --> 00:12:34,208
- [yells]

282
00:12:34,291 --> 00:12:35,958
- My turn. [grunts]

283
00:12:36,041 --> 00:12:38,083
[rumble]

284
00:12:38,166 --> 00:12:40,291
SUBARU: Okay, okay,
that's enough.

285
00:12:40,375 --> 00:12:42,625
So now that we've gotten
all our scores settled,

286
00:12:42,708 --> 00:12:45,958
I think it's time for us to
talk
about where we go from here.

287
00:12:46,041 --> 00:12:49,083
I was sure you'd be
pretty pissed, though, Ram.

288
00:12:49,166 --> 00:12:51,125
- Don't be silly.
Though I would never say

289
00:12:51,208 --> 00:12:54,666
that Master Roswaal has nothing
whatsoever to apologize for,

290
00:12:54,750 --> 00:12:57,416
I'm choosing to treat him
with kindness and respect

291
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:58,916
instead of brutality
after he's made ame--

292
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,125
- To say you have bizarre taste
is putting it mildly.

293
00:13:01,208 --> 00:13:03,000
And with wounds like yours,
what would have happened

294
00:13:03,083 --> 00:13:04,375
if I hadn't been here,
I suppose?

295
00:13:04,458 --> 00:13:07,083
- I feel grateful for everything
you did to save me,

296
00:13:07,166 --> 00:13:09,458
but I'd rather not be told
whom I should love.

297
00:13:09,541 --> 00:13:12,000
- Forget it.
Ram ain't gonna change her mind.

298
00:13:12,083 --> 00:13:15,041
But are you seriously tellin'
me
that this backstabbin' bastard

299
00:13:15,125 --> 00:13:17,375
is somebody you think
should be one of us, Boss?

300
00:13:17,458 --> 00:13:18,916
'Cause without you
and the others here,

301
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,500
the mansion and the village
would have been a disaster,

302
00:13:20,583 --> 00:13:23,166
which was all
a part of his plan!

303
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:25,166
- Believe me, I understand.

304
00:13:25,250 --> 00:13:27,125
But we're gonna need
Roswaal's strength.

305
00:13:27,208 --> 00:13:28,666
GARFIEL: What do you mean?

306
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,791
- There's no way Emilia
could ever hope to compete

307
00:13:30,875 --> 00:13:33,375
in the royal selection
without his full support.

308
00:13:33,458 --> 00:13:36,333
It's natural that you'd want to
get even with him and then some,

309
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:38,833
but we can't just smack him
around and send him off.

310
00:13:38,916 --> 00:13:41,000
- Yeah, well, I don't agree
with any of this crap.

311
00:13:41,083 --> 00:13:43,541
- I, on the other hand, am
willing to forgive the Master.

312
00:13:43,625 --> 00:13:45,500
- Come on!
This clown-faced son of a bitch

313
00:13:45,583 --> 00:13:47,833
put you and the mansion in--

314
00:13:47,916 --> 00:13:51,125
- Regardless of that,
I'm still alive and well, Garf,

315
00:13:51,208 --> 00:13:54,000
'cause you were there to
stand your ground and save me.

316
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,541
- That ain't
nothin' but hindsight!

317
00:13:55,625 --> 00:13:58,166
- I understand your hesitation,

318
00:13:58,250 --> 00:14:01,250
but I've been in the Master's
care for more than ten years.

319
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:03,583
I accepted his aid
in achieving my own goals

320
00:14:03,666 --> 00:14:05,750
while offering up my services
to him and his household.

321
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:09,000
If it wasn't
for his wisdom and guidance,

322
00:14:09,083 --> 00:14:11,208
I wouldn't be the person
that I am today.

323
00:14:11,291 --> 00:14:12,875
- Listen,
your debt and your life

324
00:14:12,958 --> 00:14:13,416
are a lot different,
all right?!

325
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:15,458
He used you and Ram to--

326
00:14:15,541 --> 00:14:17,083
- Sorry to interrupt
this debate,

327
00:14:17,166 --> 00:14:18,000
but I have concerns as well.

328
00:14:18,083 --> 00:14:20,583
It's natural that Garfiel
would be angry.

329
00:14:20,666 --> 00:14:21,666
And I did technically take part

330
00:14:21,750 --> 00:14:24,458
in the "purification ritual,"
too.

331
00:14:24,541 --> 00:14:25,750
- "Technically" take part?
With that right hook of yours,

332
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:28,416
I'd say it was
a little more than that--

333
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:29,875
- Anyway, I want to know

334
00:14:29,958 --> 00:14:33,500
exactly how much the margrave
intends to yield to us.

335
00:14:33,583 --> 00:14:35,875
- I believe your concern
is when and where

336
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,625
I might suddenly choose
to become your enemy again.

337
00:14:38,708 --> 00:14:39,583
Although, you needn't worry
about that scenario,

338
00:14:39,666 --> 00:14:41,708
I can certainly assure you.

339
00:14:41,791 --> 00:14:43,416
GARFIEL: Do you honestly
believe I'm gonna trust

340
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:45,333
a damn word you're sayin' to us?

341
00:14:45,416 --> 00:14:47,250
- No, I suppose you wouldn't.

342
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:48,958
So instead,
I'll prove it to you

343
00:14:49,041 --> 00:14:51,125
in a form that you
can actually see.

344
00:14:54,041 --> 00:14:54,958
[energy pulsing]

345
00:14:57,250 --> 00:14:59,250
[all gasp]

346
00:14:59,333 --> 00:14:59,958
- Looks like he has an oath

347
00:15:00,041 --> 00:15:02,125
that's been sealed with a curse.

348
00:15:02,208 --> 00:15:03,791
- And what does that mean?

349
00:15:03,875 --> 00:15:06,958
BEATRICE: As is customary,
an agreement can take the form

350
00:15:07,041 --> 00:15:09,958
of a contract,
an oath, or a covenant.

351
00:15:10,041 --> 00:15:12,666
While a covenant applies
to all blood relatives,

352
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:14,708
an oath is used for binding
a particular individual.

353
00:15:14,791 --> 00:15:18,416
- I was
soundly defeated in the battle.

354
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,208
Therefore, as per the agreement,

355
00:15:20,291 --> 00:15:22,541
I cannot bring harm or
distress to any of you.

356
00:15:22,625 --> 00:15:25,500
And if I were
to break this promise,

357
00:15:25,583 --> 00:15:27,166
my soul will be
forever tarnished,

358
00:15:27,250 --> 00:15:31,000
and my body will burn away
in the flames of hell.

359
00:15:31,083 --> 00:15:33,166
Then I'll descend
into nothingness.

360
00:15:33,250 --> 00:15:34,375
That is what this vow means.

361
00:15:34,458 --> 00:15:37,583
SUBARU: Wh-Why would you ever go
along with something like that?

362
00:15:37,666 --> 00:15:39,625
- Quite an odd thing to say,
coming from you,

363
00:15:39,708 --> 00:15:41,000
since you were the one

364
00:15:41,083 --> 00:15:44,000
who proposed the contest to me
in the first place.

365
00:15:44,083 --> 00:15:46,208
That is the very reason
for this mark.

366
00:15:46,291 --> 00:15:47,541
- And if I had been
the one who lost?

367
00:15:47,625 --> 00:15:50,250
- It would have been
engraved on you,

368
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:51,583
and if you'd
broken our commitment,

369
00:15:51,666 --> 00:15:53,333
only your ashes would remain.

370
00:15:53,416 --> 00:15:55,291
- What?! But still...

371
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:58,166
this should prove that
Roswaal can't betray us now.

372
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:00,208
So what do you say, Garfiel?

373
00:16:00,291 --> 00:16:01,750
- [growls]

374
00:16:01,833 --> 00:16:03,333
- Young Gar.

375
00:16:03,416 --> 00:16:05,208
What happened to Shima

376
00:16:05,291 --> 00:16:06,791
was a choice
made of her own accord.

377
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:10,333
Regardless of Young Roz,
it was necessary

378
00:16:10,416 --> 00:16:12,125
for one of us to act as the key

379
00:16:12,208 --> 00:16:14,708
and to make certain
that the barrier was undone.

380
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:15,666
- [groans]

381
00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:18,666
- Shima said she
never once felt lonely

382
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:20,625
over these past ten years,

383
00:16:20,708 --> 00:16:23,375
because she had
you there by her side.

384
00:16:23,458 --> 00:16:26,250
- Yeah, I know. I know.

385
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:28,333
Now quit lookin' like you're
about to cry, Grandma.

386
00:16:28,416 --> 00:16:29,291
It's okay.

387
00:16:31,166 --> 00:16:33,166
[inhales]

388
00:16:33,250 --> 00:16:34,541
I want you to swear to me,
Roswaal,

389
00:16:34,625 --> 00:16:37,000
no matter what happens,

390
00:16:37,083 --> 00:16:39,708
you're never gonna do
the shit you've done again.

391
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:41,208
I need to hear you say it.

392
00:16:43,458 --> 00:16:45,625
- I promise to never attempt
sacrificing anyone here

393
00:16:45,708 --> 00:16:48,416
to achieve something else again,

394
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:51,750
under any circumstances
or under any influence.

395
00:16:52,416 --> 00:16:53,791
I swear this...

396
00:16:53,875 --> 00:16:57,375
upon the very soul
of my beloved teacher.

397
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:01,083
PETRA: They might forgive you,
but I can't.

398
00:17:01,166 --> 00:17:03,500
'Cause you tried
to do something really awful

399
00:17:03,583 --> 00:17:05,250
to the people
who live in the village!

400
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:08,750
They put all their trust and
faith in you, and you just--

401
00:17:08,833 --> 00:17:11,541
Even me! I thought
you were a good person, too!

402
00:17:11,625 --> 00:17:14,083
- Your words
cause me great pain.

403
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:16,166
- They should. Even so,

404
00:17:16,250 --> 00:17:18,458
I don't want to be
thought of as the stubborn one

405
00:17:18,541 --> 00:17:21,250
who only makes things harder
for everybody here,

406
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:22,041
so I'll agree to work with you,

407
00:17:22,125 --> 00:17:24,291
but I'm never
going to forgive you,

408
00:17:24,375 --> 00:17:26,375
not ever.

409
00:17:26,458 --> 00:17:29,166
Not ever.

410
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:31,458
[sobbing]

411
00:17:31,541 --> 00:17:33,500
- I'm very proud of you,
little one.

412
00:17:35,333 --> 00:17:36,791
- I'm only gonna go along
with this for my sister,

413
00:17:36,875 --> 00:17:39,625
the old hag,
and for the little girl.

414
00:17:39,708 --> 00:17:40,666
You better remember that.

415
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:43,125
- Of course. Thank you.

416
00:17:43,208 --> 00:17:44,625
- All right, anybody else

417
00:17:44,708 --> 00:17:46,458
want to get something
off their chest?

418
00:17:46,541 --> 00:17:47,625
- I do.

419
00:17:47,708 --> 00:17:49,458
- Okay, Mili.
The floor's yours then.

420
00:17:49,541 --> 00:17:51,500
Now's your chance
to say anything you want.

421
00:17:51,583 --> 00:17:53,458
- In that case,
I'll take you up on that

422
00:17:53,541 --> 00:17:54,791
and point out
one important thing.

423
00:17:54,875 --> 00:17:57,458
- It's weird you all
haven't noticed this.

424
00:17:57,541 --> 00:17:59,333
There's something
Roswaal hasn't done yet

425
00:17:59,416 --> 00:18:00,791
that I think
is extremely necessary.

426
00:18:00,875 --> 00:18:03,083
And as far as I'm concerned,

427
00:18:03,166 --> 00:18:05,916
there's no way we can end
this discussion until he does.

428
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,208
- I'm not sure
where you're goin' with this.

429
00:18:08,291 --> 00:18:09,666
- When you do something bad,

430
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:12,708
you should apologize
for it, right?

431
00:18:14,291 --> 00:18:17,166
You've all been telling him
to "do this and say that"

432
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:19,708
to prove he honestly regrets
what he's done.

433
00:18:19,791 --> 00:18:20,958
And while you've agreed
to each of their requests

434
00:18:21,041 --> 00:18:23,541
and swore
on your teacher's soul,

435
00:18:23,625 --> 00:18:25,833
isn't there something you
should add before that, Roswaal?

436
00:18:25,916 --> 00:18:27,833
Did you say, "I'm sorry,"
even once?

437
00:18:27,916 --> 00:18:30,875
Because if so,
I didn't hear it.

438
00:18:32,208 --> 00:18:34,125
- You should apologize
for your actions.

439
00:18:34,208 --> 00:18:36,416
If you plan on working
with us from this point forward,

440
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:39,416
I think you'd have to agree
that it's the right thing to do.

441
00:18:40,541 --> 00:18:41,416
[Roswaal sighs]

442
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:44,375
I am truly sorry.

443
00:18:44,458 --> 00:18:46,000
- [grunts]

444
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:48,666
That's enough for me.

445
00:18:53,708 --> 00:18:56,125
[chamber music playing]

446
00:18:58,833 --> 00:19:00,416
[crowd murmuring]

447
00:19:05,875 --> 00:19:08,458
SUBARU: Conferment
of knighthood?

448
00:19:08,541 --> 00:19:10,541
They're really
going all out here, aren't they?

449
00:19:10,625 --> 00:19:12,708
- Oh, come now.
I thought this was the moment

450
00:19:12,791 --> 00:19:14,875
you'd spent
so much time waiting for.

451
00:19:14,958 --> 00:19:17,208
- Sure it is,
but having these people host it

452
00:19:17,291 --> 00:19:19,375
just seems like
a little much to me, you know?

453
00:19:19,458 --> 00:19:22,625
- Well, the Miload family is
a branch of the Mathers
family,

454
00:19:22,708 --> 00:19:24,500
and their leader, Annerose,

455
00:19:24,583 --> 00:19:27,166
just happens to be
head over heels for Miss Emilia.

456
00:19:29,416 --> 00:19:32,500
- I see. Now, what was it
you wanted to tell me?

457
00:19:32,583 --> 00:19:36,000
- I have a goal, and that's
to reunite with my teacher.

458
00:19:36,083 --> 00:19:38,791
- I'm not sure I understand.
She was there in the coffin,

459
00:19:38,875 --> 00:19:40,375
wasn't she?
Haven't you already--

460
00:19:40,458 --> 00:19:42,875
- It seems
you're a bit confused.

461
00:19:42,958 --> 00:19:45,416
This reunion can only take place

462
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:47,958
when she lives and breathes,
when she houses a soul.

463
00:19:48,041 --> 00:19:50,875
That is my desire and
dearest wish, Subaru.

464
00:19:50,958 --> 00:19:53,583
- And is there a way to do that?

465
00:19:53,666 --> 00:19:55,583
- I'm now
without the Tome of Wisdom,

466
00:19:55,666 --> 00:19:57,875
and I'm bound by the mark
of the oath,

467
00:19:57,958 --> 00:19:59,208
but having said that,

468
00:19:59,291 --> 00:20:01,583
I've no intention
of ever giving up on her.

469
00:20:01,666 --> 00:20:02,625
- All right,
but what good is that gonna do?

470
00:20:02,708 --> 00:20:04,416
- It's simple, really.

471
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:09,125
I intend to keep my eye on you,
following your every move.

472
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:12,625
See, you made
the rather arrogant decision

473
00:20:12,708 --> 00:20:15,458
that you would lose nothing and
simply pick up all the pieces.

474
00:20:15,541 --> 00:20:18,166
By doing so,

475
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:20,958
you'll surely continue
to be hurt from now on.

476
00:20:21,041 --> 00:20:22,958
You'll lose things repeatedly,

477
00:20:23,041 --> 00:20:25,791
and each time that you
manage to get them back,

478
00:20:25,875 --> 00:20:28,833
you'll gain
new, invisible wounds.

479
00:20:28,916 --> 00:20:30,958
I know that if I lost anyone,

480
00:20:31,041 --> 00:20:33,666
I wouldn't hesitate
to destroy everything.

481
00:20:33,750 --> 00:20:36,250
I will not compromise.

482
00:20:36,333 --> 00:20:40,583
Nothing can lead me back to
my teacher but you, understand,

483
00:20:40,666 --> 00:20:42,458
and the path only you can take.

484
00:20:42,541 --> 00:20:43,625
- [crowd murmuring]
- It's Emilia.

485
00:20:43,708 --> 00:20:45,500
- She looks stunning.

486
00:20:45,583 --> 00:20:47,458
- What a lovely dress.
- Wow.

487
00:20:47,541 --> 00:20:48,916
- So beautiful.

488
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,791
- [gasps]

489
00:20:50,875 --> 00:20:53,541
- And now
we'll begin the ceremony

490
00:20:53,625 --> 00:20:54,708
of the conferment of knighthood.

491
00:20:54,791 --> 00:20:58,000
Subaru Natsuki, come forth.

492
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:01,541
- Congratulations, Subaru.

493
00:21:01,625 --> 00:21:04,416
You've earned the praise
of the witch's disciple.

494
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:06,666
You've won a victory,

495
00:21:06,750 --> 00:21:08,458
for today at least.

496
00:21:08,541 --> 00:21:10,375
[silence]

497
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:24,625
[sword rattles]

498
00:21:27,666 --> 00:21:28,916
[organ music playing]

499
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,166
- The sun that looks down
upon a brilliant world,

500
00:21:31,250 --> 00:21:35,291
the stars that keep watch
when the world sleeps,

501
00:21:35,375 --> 00:21:39,625
the wind, to the water,
